 Justification:
 The FY 2026 request for CV-22 includes $78,713 thousand of discretionary and $100,329 thousand of mandatory (reconciliation) for a total of $179,042 thousand. The mandatory funds capability and survivability
 modification efforts. Further information for this reconciliation request is provided in Section 20007 (Air Superiority) of the Reconciliation Exhibit.

 The primary modification budgeted in FY 2026 is the Block C/20 Upgrade that primarily focuses on an improved proprotor gearbox (PRGB) which is triple-melted steel that will reduce the likelihood of material
 defects in critical gears and bearings. PRGB enhancements vastly improves safety, reliability and operational readiness for the entire V-22 enterprise.




