providing flexible, long-range, advanced, anti-surface capability against high-threat maritime targets. LRASM (AGM-158C) achieved Early Operational Capability (EOC) in December 2018 on the USAF B-1
Lancer and EOC on the USN F/A-18E/F Super Hornet in November 2019. The USN is the lead service for the LRASM program.

LRASM is highly leveraged on the design of the Joint Air-to-Surface Standoff Missile-Extended Range (JASSM-ER). LRASM and JASSM-ER have over 70% hardware commonality and share the same
production assembly line. The USAF and USN jointly procure LRASMs via a USAF contract that benefits from cost savings when aligned with JASSM-ER procurements.




