 Justification:
 The FY 2026 increase allows the procurement of an additional three (3) 3DELRR systems on the basis of the re-negotiated firm fixed price cost structure of the procurement contract, and scales up the interim
 contractor support to accommodate the additional fielded systems until an organic USAF support capability is established. This investment will allow for the replacement of the AN/TPS-75 and provides the
 warfighter with a reliable and threat relevant long range radar system.

 Production Units: FY 2026 funds will procure three (3) 3DELRR systems, to include the necessary logistics and program support associated with the delivery of the system.

 Direct Mission Support (DMS) Equipment: FY 2026 funds will procure equipment associated with the 3DELRR systems. Equipment includes Prime Movers, Generators, and necessary crypto & support
 equipment. Prime Movers and generators are sent directly to the operational units. The remaining equipment is sent to Lockheed Martin as Government Furnished Property (GFP) for integration with the TPY-4.

 Interim Contractor Support (ICS): FY 2026 funds will provide ICS to fielded units




