 Justification:
 The program increase in FY26 allows for the procurement of technology refresh assets to replace sensor systems with end of life components to maintain critical surveillance in support of homeland defense
 mission in the National Capitol Region.

 FY26 activities will include but are not limited to the following:

 Fielding operational sensors; addressing emerging sensor capabilities; updating system infrastructure such as a system integrated lab and system health and monitoring centralized data processing capability to
 support operations for NORAD/NORTHCOM; supporting technical refresh of fielded sites; upgrading hardware and software to seamlessly integrate new and emerging sensors, data, and technologies; procuring
 end items and spares that do not qualify for Centralized Asset Management (CAM) funding; funding program and direct mission support providing management, engineering, cost and technical support for
 the program office; supporting potential diminishing manufacturing sources, material shortages, obsolescence solutions, sparing, and recapitalization; and procuring key components of each site that require
 significant lead time items.




