INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_AIRFOR_NA_L0059$$, 2026, $$Air Force$$, $$PROC_AIRFOR$$, $$AIRFOR$$, NULL, $$59$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

 Justification:
 PE 0303133F HIGH FREQUENCY GLOBAL COMMUNICATIONS SYSTEM (HFGCS)

 FY 2026 procurement funding for the High Frequency Global Communications System (HFGCS) focuses on modernizing the radio/network infrastructure and replacing aging antenna systems across its global
 network of 13 ground stations and two network control stations. The radio/network infrastructure modernization effort prioritizes replacing outdated components with commercially available technology to enhance
 capabilities and ensure long-term system viability. This includes upgrading the Unified Capabilities/Audio Communications Functionality (UC/ACF) switch to a modern system, transitioning the HFGCS network
 to a more robust and flexible cloud environment. Funding will also replace the current 30-year-old high power amplifiers (HPAs) with modern equipment to reduce sustainment costs, high failure rates, and
 incompatibility with advanced HF waveforms. Additionally, funding will support the installation of RT2200A radios, upgrading from obsolete legacy radios to modern, software-defined radios with enhanced
 capabilities, aligning with the Department of Defense's (DoD's) High Frequency (HF) modernization strategy.

 Beyond these upgrades, FY 2026 funding will also support ongoing HF modernization efforts, including implementing robust waveforms and techniques to increase network resiliency and reliability. It will also
 address diminishing manufacturing sources and material shortages (DMSMS) and obsolescence by procuring replacements or identifying alternative solutions for aging or obsolete components. Finally, it will
 fund hardware updates and integration to meet mandated cybersecurity requirements.

 The High Frequency Global Antenna Replacement program replaces antennas across the enterprise that have degraded after over 35 years of operation in harsh climate conditions. This project prioritizes
 locations based on need and operational requirements while also addressing DMSMS and obsolescence for critical antenna components.

 Finally, FY 2026 funding will also cover program support costs including program management and administration, engineering, cybersecurity initiatives, travel, operational testing, and technical interchanges.

 In FY 2026, HFGCS received a $0.046 million for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration in alignment with Executive Order 14222, "Implementing
 the President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiative."

 PE 0305158F TACTICAL TERMINAL (TT)
 FY 2026 efforts include procuring and integrating security-upgraded IBS-compatible tactical terminals with the most recent software to ensure that AF weapons systems can transmit to/receive the IBS broadcast
 directly.

 A phased acquisition strategy will be employed to procure 1036 tactical terminals, directly supporting the efficient integration of these terminals with corresponding weapon systems. To maintain optimal inventory
 levels and adapt to evolving operational needs, the total terminal requirement will be reviewed annually.

 PE 0102325F Advanced Early Warning System (AEWS)

