 Justification:
 PE 0102325F Atmospheric Early Warning System (AEWS) - Joint Surveillance System (JSS)
 FY26 Funding provides procurement and installation of aging AN/FPS-117 radomes supporting the AEWS JSS.

 Replacement of the JSS portion of AN/FPS-117 fleet of radomes (16 total) within the PACAF theater with commercially available composite radomes is required. Funding supports procurement of manufacturing,
 installation/integration, site surveys, government acceptance, travel, shipping, over & above if required, spare hardware, technical reports, and contractor services personnel to support the logistics and validation
 of radomes. Existing radomes are 20 years beyond their design life, resulting in excessive delamination, increased maintenance costs, and risk to the radar systems. A prior radome collapse at an AEWS site due
 to snow underscores a catastrophic deficiency and personnel safety risk. Radome replacement is crucial to ensuring continued operational readiness and preventing potential loss of life.

 PE 0102412F Atmospheric Early Warning System (AEWS) - North Warning System (NWS)
 FY26 Funding provides replacement of aging AN/FPS-117 and AN/FPS-124 radomes supporting the AEWS NWS.

 Replacement of the NWS portion of AN/FPS-117 fleet of radomes (10 total) and AN/FPS-124 fleet of radomes (36 total) within the PACAF and Canadian theaters with commercially available composite radomes
 is required. Funding supports procurement of manufacturing, installation/integration, site surveys, government acceptance, travel, shipping, over & above if required, spare hardware, technical reports, and
 contractor services personnel to support the logistics and validation of radomes. Existing radomes are 20 years beyond their design life, resulting in excessive delamination, increased maintenance costs, and risk
 to the radar systems. A prior radome collapse at an Atmospheric Early Warning System (AEWS) site due to snow underscores a catastrophic deficiency and personnel safety risk. Radome replacement is crucial
 to ensuring continued operational readiness and preventing potential loss of life.

 PE 0804701F ADVANCED PILOT TRAINING T-7A - P-40A
 Advanced Pilot Training T-7A Facility Communication Equipment funding for an antenna farm for T-7A data links. No funding requested in FY 2025 and FY 2026.

 PE 0205219F MQ-9 UAV
 MQ-9 Reaper Remotely Piloted Aircraft (RPA) Squadron Operations Centers (SOC):                                                                                                                                                 No FY26 funds requested.


