 Description:
 PE 0102412F Atmospheric Early Warning System (AEWS) of systems.

 Joint Surveillance System (JSS) and North Warning System (NWS) within the Atmospheric Early Warning System (AEWS) of systems, continue to age and require innovative solutions to be implemented to
 combat obsolescence. These solutions include Digital Array Row Transceivers (DARTs), DART cable mod kit, data register bypass cables, Radar Data Processor (RDP) (S7 and Second Edition), Frequency
 Synthesizer technical refresh, and Local Controller Control Unit (LCCU) technical refreshes. These efforts are necessary to reduce reliance to ensure operational availability and compliance with Authority To
 Operate (ATO) requirements by resolving obsolete components, mitigation of Diminishing Manufacturing Sources and Material Shortages (DMSMS) and subsequent system performance issues. Deployment of
 the Archer Remote Sensing System is underway and requires funding to move from prototype to production. Modernization efforts are necessary to mitigate risks associated with the use of Commercial Off The
 Shelf (COTS) components. A&AS personnel are also necessary to manage workload associated with the complexity of acquiring a program developed using rapid prototyping and fielding strategies.



 PE 0102325F Atmospheric Early Warning System (AEWS) of systems.

 Joint Surveillance System (JSS) and North Warning System (NWS) within the Atmospheric Early Warning System (AEWS) of systems, continue to age and require innovative solutions to be implemented to
 combat obsolescence. These solutions include Digital Array Row Transceivers (DARTs), data register bypass cables, and Mission Software technical refreshes. These efforts are necessary to reduce reliance
 to ensure operational availability and compliance with Authority To Operate (ATO) requirements by resolving obsolete components, mitigation of Diminishing Manufacturing Sources and Material Shortages
 (DMSMS) and subsequent system performance issues.

 PE 0305114F Air Traffic Control and Landing Systems (ATCALS) - Low Cost Modifications

 Fixed base and deployable ATCALS low cost modifications are initiated to resolve Diminishing Manufacturing Source (DMS) issues and minor system deficiencies/improvements identified through the ATCALS
 Weapon System Review-Executive Council (WSR-EC), policy TO 00-35D-54 Deficiency Reports, and Material Improvement initiatives. Supporting activities include, but are not limited to annual low cost
 modifications unforeseen sustainment activities, obsolescence scans, Diminishing Manufacturing Sources/Material Shortage studies/resolution, Technical Support Services (TSS) which includes Engineering
 Support, Site Specific Issue Resolution, Trouble Reports, Investigation Requests, and the Product Support Library. The return on investment for these low-cost modifications will be realized immediately through


