 Justification:
 FY 2026 will fund procurement of Fuels Support Equipment in support of Pre-Positioned War Reserve Materiel Global Theater requirements. Planned quantities could change due to price increases, inflation, and
 supply chain fluctuations.

 FY 2026 includes $2.804M for the procurement of Regional Basing Cluster Pre-positioning (RBCP) Fuels Generation Capabilities and are critical to Agile Combat Employment in support of the Pacific Deterrence
 Initiative (PDI). Planned procurements will be remaining requirements from the previous fiscal year and could include Aerial Bulk Fuel Delivery System / Fuels Bladders / All Terrain Berm Liners.

 FY 2026 includes $3.557M in support of non-WRM Operational Fuels Requirements.

 FY 2026 request was reduced by $0.088M for Advisory and Assistance Services to promote efficiencies and advance the policies of the Administration in alignment with Executive Order 14222, implementing the
 President's Department of Government Efficiency Cost Efficiency Initiatives.

 FY 2024 changes made after the FY 2025 PB submission include Congressional reduction of $74.519M and reprogramming reduction of $32.217M (DoD Serial No. FY 24-11 PA); changes include a decrease in
 the number of procurement quantities planned.

 Fuels Support Equipment assets significantly impact Contested Logistics and provide a cost-effective mix of investments that operationalize the Agile Combat Employment (ACE) concept (AFDN 1-21) in the
 Indo-Pacific. ACE is a proactive and reactive scheme of maneuver that shifts generation of airpower from large, fixed centralized bases to networks of smaller, dispersed bases. Prepositioned capabilities, ashore
 and afloat, place military equipment and supplies at or near the point of planned use to ensure timely support of Expeditionary Air Forces and other specific forces during the initial phases of an operation. These
 assets provide combatant commanders with initial capabilities and materiel until establishment of a mature and sustained Strategic/Theater Distribution Network (TDP) (CJSCI 4310.01F).

 This program performs a critical role in Combatant Command (CCMD) requirements to support 5 major Operations Plans (OPLANs) and ensures the objectives of the National Defense Strategy can be executed.

 The Fuels Support Equipment program adheres to guidance:
 10 U.S.C. 2229, Strategic Policy on Prepositioning of Materiel and Equipment.

 CJSCI 4310.01F: Prepositioned capabilities, ashore and afloat, place military equipment and supplies at or near the point of planned use to ensure timely support of Expeditionary Air Forces and other specific
 forces during the initial phases of an operation. These assets provide combatant commanders with initial capabilities and materiel until establishment of a mature and sustained Strategic/Theater Distribution
 Network (TDP).




